  "texts": [
    "Reaction role assignments that distinguish reactants, reagents, catalysts, and solvents are sometimes used in downstream tasks such as reaction condition recommendation.",
    "[55] [56] [57] The reaction role of a compound is context-dependent, e.g., a chemical can serve as a solvent or a reactant in different reactions, and not explicitly stated in procedure text, so this is also not a pure information extraction task.",
    "However, since this implicit information is included in fine-tuning, the fine-tuned model learns the conventions about role assignment in a generalizable way, and the inferred assignment is directly available in the reaction_role field.",
    "Since each Compound message is allowed to have only one reaction_role, the reaction role assignment is a standard classification problem.",
    "While the ORD data schema has more than 10 types of reaction roles defined to cover a variety of situations, in this dataset only three are used for input compounds (CATALYST, REACTANT, SOLVENT)."
  ],
